sentences: Ma käin jooksma igal päeval rannaliiva peal.
Jõuluvanemad on alati väga juba ja teevad palju rõhku jooksude peale.
Mees pani jalgratta kasti ja alustas kiiret jooksu.
context: The word 'jooksed' is the second person plural form of the verb 'jooksema,' which means to run or jog in Estonian. It typically refers to physical activity where a person moves quickly on foot, often for exercise, sport, or recreation.
